related_ngsl.related_word_forms: organise, organised, organises, organising, organized, organizes, organizing

examples.en: Students need to learn how to organize their work.
We must finally organize our files properly.
I'll get you organized in no time.
He doesn't need you to organize his life for him.
I'll ask my secretary to organize some refreshments.
They can't be arsed to organize it properly.
Who else can we rope in to organize the tour?
I can organize myself okay enough.
You need to learn to organize better.
I packed a bag and organized some food.
Organize yourself to arrive at places on time.
The books were organized on the shelves according to their size.
We are learning about how genes are organized.
They hired a professional to help organize their wedding.
The scientists need to organize themselves and work as a team.
I stupidly agreed to organize the party.
They had to organize to hold out (in the struggle).
I spent some time organizing my closet last weekend.
He was delegated to organize and lead the expedition.
The program was designed to organize and manipulate large amounts of data.
The lawyer helped to organize a group of parents who took action for their children.
I'd like to see you organize a conference!
She organized people to work for social justice.
He encouraged them to organize for social justice.
They organized a meeting between the teachers and students.
The company has tried to prevent the workers from organizing.

With blind obedience, I allowed my father to organize my life.
